    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "A minimum working example on my end would be adding `solc = \"0.8.13\"` in `foundry.toml`:\r\n```\r\n[profile.default]\r\nsolc = \"0.8.13\"\r\nsrc = 'src'\r\nout = 'out'\r\nlibs = ['lib']\r\n\r\n# See more config options https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/tree/master/config\r\n```\r\nand then I could deploy & verify via:\r\n`forge create --rpc-url <rpc_url> --constructor-args <args> --private-key <private_key> src/<name>.sol:<name> --etherscan-api-key <api_key> --verify`.\r\n\r\nWould get the error above when verifying if the compiler version is not explicitly stated. \r\n",
